01:38.840 --> 01:41.753
So, you'll never guess
who turned up yesterday.

01:41.920 --> 01:43.194
Go on.

01:43.360 --> 01:45.715
- Madelyn.
- Madelyn showed up?

01:45.880 --> 01:49.191
Completely out of the blue.
I haven't seen her in 15 years.

01:49.360 --> 01:52.000
And there she was,
standing on the doorstep,

01:52.160 --> 01:53.798
- all gussied up.
- Ha-ha-ha.

01:53.960 --> 01:56.395
And that's a sight
I thought I'd never see again.

01:56.560 --> 01:58.392
What did she want?

01:58.560 --> 02:00.517
20,000 bucks.

02:00.720 --> 02:02.631
Ha-ha-ha! 20,000 bucks?

02:02.800 --> 02:05.952
15 years of back alimony.
I said, "What alimony?

02:06.120 --> 02:08.555
"When we split up, I gave you
whatever money we had,

02:08.720 --> 02:09.994
"and you took the car.

02:10.160 --> 02:11.434
We agreed, that was that."

02:11.600 --> 02:13.193
Geez, not even Mae asked for that,

02:13.400 --> 02:15.198
and she wanted me to pay
for a chauffeur.

02:15.400 --> 02:17.630
It's because our pictures
are plastered all over town.

02:17.800 --> 02:19.837
Probably some lawyer's bright idea.

02:20.000 --> 02:21.991
Well, in any case, I haven't got it.

02:22.200 --> 02:24.760
Myrtle cleaned me out when we split.

02:24.920 --> 02:27.070
You been down to Tijuana?

02:27.240 --> 02:29.470
- Why you ask?
- We had a few days off.

02:29.640 --> 02:31.199
Well, as a matter of fact,

02:31.360 --> 02:33.078
I did take a little trip down there

02:33.240 --> 02:36.471
with Mysterious Montague,
trying to win some back.

02:36.640 --> 02:39.314
Not entirely successfully, unfortunately.

02:39.480 --> 02:41.357
Hey, when is your contract up?

02:41.520 --> 02:43.158
We should ask for a little more money.

02:43.320 --> 02:44.435
A little more? Are you kidding?

02:44.640 --> 02:45.835
Charlie, Buster, Harold,

02:46.000 --> 02:47.877
they get ten times what Hal pays us.

02:48.040 --> 02:49.678
Well, they own their own pictures.

02:49.840 --> 02:51.672
Exactly. That's what we're gonna do.

02:51.840 --> 02:53.114
Hey, boys. How's it going?

02:53.280 --> 02:54.873
Georgie. We're going shark fishing.

02:55.040 --> 02:57.156
Mr. Laurel doesn't know it yet,
but he's the bait.

02:58.720 --> 03:00.950
Now, how are we gonna do that?
We're under contract.

03:01.120 --> 03:02.758
We can't just change the terms.

03:02.920 --> 03:06.276
Well, we stick together,
we renegotiate with Hal,

03:06.440 --> 03:08.158
get a bigger slice of the pie.

03:08.320 --> 03:10.834
If that doesn't work,
then we walk and set up on our own.

03:11.040 --> 03:13.714
Oh, I don't know.
I mean, I'd love to own our pictures,

03:13.920 --> 03:15.991
but it just doesn't
seem like the right time.

03:16.160 --> 03:17.514
I've got a lot going on.

03:17.680 --> 03:18.909
This overhead is killing me.

03:19.080 --> 03:20.878
- Hi, Babe. Ha, ha.
- Hello, girls.

03:21.040 --> 03:22.758
Hey, guys, you're wanted on set.

03:22.920 --> 03:24.558
Ah, Burgess, just the man.

03:24.760 --> 03:26.273
Listen, take this to our friend.

03:26.440 --> 03:27.999
Tell him I want it on Bold Venture,

03:28.160 --> 03:29.912
the fourth race at Santa Anita,
on the nose.

03:30.080 --> 03:31.195
There's something in there for you.

03:31.360 --> 03:32.919
Would you do it right away, please?

03:33.080 --> 03:35.151
- It's about to start.
- Okay. Thank you, Mr. Hardy.

03:35.360 --> 03:36.839
You'll be fine, Babe.

03:37.000 --> 03:40.755
Just lay off the horses
and don't get married again.

03:40.920 --> 03:42.957
Oh, I didn't tell you.

03:43.120 --> 03:46.158
- I proposed to Lucille.
- Scripty Lucille?

03:46.320 --> 03:48.311
- Yes.
- Damn.

03:48.480 --> 03:50.118
And she said yes.

03:50.280 --> 03:52.476
Ah. That's great news, Babe.

03:52.640 --> 03:54.392
She needs a head examining, but...

03:54.560 --> 03:57.029
- Ha-ha-ha.
- ...great for you.

03:57.640 --> 03:59.233
Here.

03:59.400 --> 04:00.834
I'm never getting married again.

04:01.000 --> 04:02.752
I'm just gonna find a woman I don't like

04:02.920 --> 04:04.069
and buy her a house.

04:04.240 --> 04:05.833
Ha! That's a good one.

04:06.000 --> 04:09.231
Listen, I can't afford
to fool around with my income,

04:09.400 --> 04:12.597
so don't antagonize Hal,
will you, please?

04:12.760 --> 04:14.751
I don't like to talk about business.

04:14.920 --> 04:16.240
Not when we're working.

04:16.440 --> 04:18.430
I promise I'll be as nice as pie,

04:18.600 --> 04:20.432
- so long as he doesn't show up.
- Heh.

04:20.600 --> 04:22.273
They're ready for us, girls.

04:22.440 --> 04:24.795
What's this? Our rodeos are getting
a lot more interesting.

04:24.960 --> 04:28.430
You know,
I don't miss England one little bit.

04:28.600 --> 04:30.318
- Hello, girls.
- Hi.

04:30.480 --> 04:32.312
- Hello.
- Heh, heh.

04:32.480 --> 04:35.199
Oh, by the way, I've chartered a sailboat

04:35.360 --> 04:36.714
to Catalina this Saturday.

04:36.920 --> 04:38.513
- You want to come?
- Ah...

04:38.680 --> 04:41.672
I gotta work on the gags
for the bar routine.

04:41.880 --> 04:45.919
- Ah, be a lot of nice girls there.
- Yeah?

04:46.080 --> 04:49.675
Miss Myrna Loy will be on board,
among others.

04:49.840 --> 04:51.751
Ah, yeah, well, all right, maybe I'll come.

04:51.920 --> 04:53.911
What are all these Romans doing here?

04:54.080 --> 04:56.435
I don't know.
Maybe there's a sale at the Forum.

04:58.240 --> 05:00.914
You've got a million of 'em, don't you?

05:01.080 --> 05:03.594
Hey, Lucille,
have you got my sides over there?

05:03.760 --> 05:05.876
- Right here, Mr. Horne.
- Thank you.

05:06.040 --> 05:07.474
A sweet for my sweet.

05:07.640 --> 05:09.677
Oh, thank you, Babe.

05:11.360 --> 05:13.351
Listen, let's not talk about leaving.

05:13.520 --> 05:15.511
Let's just try to get ourselves a raise.

05:15.680 --> 05:17.557
- Hey, Jimmie.
- Give you a raise?

05:17.720 --> 05:21.429
He'd rather lower Hollywood,
and that's a Scotsman talking.

05:21.600 --> 05:24.399
- Going for a smoke.
- Heh, heh.

05:25.760 --> 05:27.034
That's it, Stan.

05:27.200 --> 05:28.634
We're through.

05:28.800 --> 05:30.711
I'm throwing the moral clause at you.

05:30.880 --> 05:31.995
Morning, Hal.

05:32.160 --> 05:34.197
Another fight at his place last night.

05:34.360 --> 05:36.795
One of the neighbors sees
Ruthie sock him in the mouth,

05:36.960 --> 05:38.189
so they call the cops.

05:38.400 --> 05:39.959
She found out about Vera.

05:40.120 --> 05:42.794
Yeah, it cost me 500 bucks
to keep it out of the papers,

05:42.960 --> 05:44.712
and that's coming out of your paycheck.

05:44.880 --> 05:47.440
You signed a contract
not to prejudice Hal Roach Studios.

05:47.600 --> 05:49.432
Well, you know all about prejudice.

05:49.600 --> 05:50.829
How's your pal Mussolini,

05:51.000 --> 05:52.513
the one you were going to go
into business with

05:52.680 --> 05:55.399
before he started bombing
all those poor people in Africa?

05:55.560 --> 05:57.153
You see? All he wants to do is fight.

05:57.320 --> 05:58.719
What are you looking for, Stan?

05:58.920 --> 05:59.955
I'm looking for a fair price

06:00.120 --> 06:01.918
for a Laurel and Hardy picture,
and you know it.

06:02.080 --> 06:04.549
Our pictures sell all around the world,
and we haven't got a dime.

06:04.720 --> 06:06.154
That's because
you keep getting divorced!

06:06.320 --> 06:08.470
No, it's because you're a cheapskate
who got rich off our backs.

06:08.680 --> 06:10.114
- Oh, come on, now, Stan.
- He is.

06:10.280 --> 06:12.351
He's a Cheapskate, a skinflint
and a... and a parvenu.

06:12.520 --> 06:14.670
- A parvenu?
- He thinks, because my contract's up

06:14.840 --> 06:17.150
and yours isn't, that I won't be able
to go anyplace else

06:17.320 --> 06:18.833
and I'll have to take what he's offering.

06:19.000 --> 06:20.274
- Wait, wait, wait, wait.
- Mr. Roach?

06:20.480 --> 06:21.914
What's a parvenu?

06:22.080 --> 06:24.037
Well, it's someone
who started out with nothing,

06:24.200 --> 06:25.554
got rich but has no class.

06:25.720 --> 06:26.994
Look it up in the dictionary, Hal.

06:27.160 --> 06:28.719
There's a picture of you.

06:28.880 --> 06:30.598
Oh, you think you're
some sort of smart-ass, huh?

06:30.760 --> 06:32.159
Well, guess what. I'm smarter.

06:32.320 --> 06:35.312
Has he told you yet?
We're setting up on our own.

06:36.320 --> 06:38.311
Hal, it might be best

06:38.480 --> 06:41.199
if you could see your way
to a small raise.

06:41.360 --> 06:43.237
You're setting up on your own, huh?

06:43.400 --> 06:44.913
Well, how about this?

06:45.080 --> 06:46.593
Babe's still under contract with me,

06:46.800 --> 06:48.029
and I ain't releasing him.

06:48.200 --> 06:49.998
You can't have Hardy without Laurel.

06:50.160 --> 06:52.151
Oh, well, that's what you think.

06:52.320 --> 06:54.709
Hal, uh, could you maybe
continue this some other time?

06:54.880 --> 06:57.713
Unless you want to pay
for an extra day, of course.

06:57.880 --> 06:59.757
Go ahead, shoot. Go ahead.

06:59.920 --> 07:01.831
Okay, so we're on
a wide two-shot here, Stan,

07:02.000 --> 07:02.956
just like you wanted.

07:03.120 --> 07:04.474
Then I'm gonna pull back...

07:04.640 --> 07:06.119
- What are you checking with him for?
- Well...

07:06.320 --> 07:07.390
You're the director.

07:07.560 --> 07:09.676
- Direct.
- Ugh.

07:10.400 --> 07:13.472
Next person you'll be hearing from
is my lawyer.

07:13.640 --> 07:15.199
Positions, everyone.

07:15.360 --> 07:18.113
Comedy Western.
Who came up with that smart idea?

07:19.480 --> 07:21.198
Well, that went well.

07:21.360 --> 07:23.636
So, uh, who else is
gonna be on this boat?

07:23.800 --> 07:24.870
Clark Gable, some other people.

07:25.040 --> 07:26.633
- No, no, no. Women.
- Oh.

07:26.840 --> 07:28.478
Carole Lombard.
She's friends with Myrna.

07:28.640 --> 07:30.278
Oh. Okay, I'm gonna come.

07:30.440 --> 07:32.397
- Oh, good.
- All right, show's over.

07:32.560 --> 07:34.358
Let's, uh, roll sound.

07:34.520 --> 07:36.796
- I said roll sound.
- Speed.

07:36.960 --> 07:38.030
Roll camera.

07:38.200 --> 07:40.077
- Ready, boys?
- Quiet, please.

07:40.240 --> 07:41.753
"Way Out West," scene 12, take one.

07:41.920 --> 07:43.319
Oh, what's after the curtseys?

07:43.520 --> 07:45.591
Uh, after the curtseys,
knee bend, then turn and shake.

07:45.760 --> 07:47.034
